1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:04,295
[brazen music playing]

2
00:00:09,884 --> 00:00:12,429
[electronic blipping]

3
00:00:16,016 --> 00:00:19,853
[Marcus] We have to capture Merelli
so we can take Rogue Crescent down.

4
00:00:19,936 --> 00:00:21,813
[Elaine] <i>How did you know I was even here?</i>

5
00:00:21,896 --> 00:00:23,189
I have a strong sense of smell.

6
00:00:23,273 --> 00:00:25,567
[Elaine] <i>There's something</i>
<i>you're not telling us.</i>

7
00:00:25,650 --> 00:00:26,735
[Atoy] <i>The same goes for you.</i>

8
00:00:27,444 --> 00:00:30,447
[Vilma] <i>There's something strange about</i>
<i>that guy. I bet he has a different agenda.</i>

9
00:00:30,530 --> 00:00:32,824
[Elaine] <i>Did you see where he went?</i>

10
00:00:32,907 --> 00:00:34,576
The target has arrived.

11
00:00:34,659 --> 00:00:35,660
[Elaine] Who are you, really?

12
00:00:35,744 --> 00:00:37,120
[Atoy] <i>Target is moving ahead of schedule.</i>

13
00:00:37,203 --> 00:00:39,998
<i>I advise you instruct</i>
<i>the strike team to move now.</i>

14
00:00:40,081 --> 00:00:41,708
[in English] You want some crabs?

15
00:00:41,791 --> 00:00:42,709
Very, very good crabs.

16
00:00:42,792 --> 00:00:44,669
[in English] You don't look like
you're selling crabs, mister.

17
00:00:44,753 --> 00:00:46,880
PREVIOUSLY

18
00:00:46,963 --> 00:00:48,548
[goon] Drop your gun!

19
00:00:48,631 --> 00:00:50,008
- Or else, I'll kill this child!
- Sir, help me!

20
00:00:50,759 --> 00:00:52,177
[Merelli] Kill that boy… now!

21
00:00:52,260 --> 00:00:54,179
[Ponyo wails]

22
00:00:58,183 --> 00:01:00,435
- [gun firing]
- [explosion]

23
00:01:00,518 --> 00:01:02,437
[screaming] Get that kid!

24
00:01:02,520 --> 00:01:05,732
- [thudding]
- [grunting]

25
00:01:08,610 --> 00:01:10,653
[swooshes]

26
00:01:11,738 --> 00:01:13,823
[swooshes]

27
00:01:15,533 --> 00:01:20,955
[somber music playing]

28
00:01:33,468 --> 00:01:35,762
Sir, sir, help me.

29
00:01:35,845 --> 00:01:37,305
My name is Rudy.

30
00:01:37,388 --> 00:01:38,848
They got Ponyo.

31
00:01:38,932 --> 00:01:41,309
I am begging you. We have to save him.

32
00:01:44,896 --> 00:01:45,855
Let's go!

33
00:01:47,690 --> 00:01:49,317
[inquisitive music playing]

34
00:01:49,400 --> 00:01:51,194
- Do you know how to use this?
- I do.

35
00:01:51,277 --> 00:01:52,362
Let's go.

36
00:01:55,615 --> 00:01:57,617
[inquisitive music continues]

37
00:02:09,420 --> 00:02:10,588
Help!

38
00:02:10,672 --> 00:02:12,757
What are you going to do to me?!

39
00:02:13,341 --> 00:02:15,385
Where are you taking me?!

40
00:02:15,468 --> 00:02:17,303
[in English] Shut up!

41
00:02:17,387 --> 00:02:18,805
[in English] Boss,
what do we do with that kid?

42
00:02:18,888 --> 00:02:19,889
[in English] Throw him off.

43
00:02:20,473 --> 00:02:21,558
- Help!
- [in English] Go!

44
00:02:21,641 --> 00:02:24,310
- Come on! Get up!
- I don't want to!

45
00:02:24,394 --> 00:02:25,395
[in English] Come on!

46
00:02:25,478 --> 00:02:26,354
- [in English] Go! Go!
- No!

47
00:02:26,437 --> 00:02:29,023
- [in English] Shut up!
- [Ponyo bawling]

48
00:02:29,107 --> 00:02:30,441
[Ponyo] I don't want to!

49
00:02:35,738 --> 00:02:37,740
[bullet plinks]

50
00:02:37,824 --> 00:02:43,621
[brazen music playing]

51
00:02:47,709 --> 00:02:48,668
[in English] Shoot him!

52
00:02:53,214 --> 00:02:54,632
Help me!

53
00:02:54,716 --> 00:02:57,886
- [gun firing]
- [bullets plinking]

54
00:02:57,969 --> 00:02:59,095
[Merelli, in English] Kill them!

55
00:03:05,685 --> 00:03:09,731
[brazen music continues]

56
00:03:13,568 --> 00:03:14,861
[in English] Kill them!

57
00:03:29,417 --> 00:03:31,210
[bullets plinking]

58
00:03:32,378 --> 00:03:34,213
Sir Rudy, we have to stop.

59
00:03:34,297 --> 00:03:36,007
I'll move to another spot.

60
00:03:36,090 --> 00:03:40,929
[brazen music continues]

61
00:04:03,618 --> 00:04:07,580
[dramatic music playing]

62
00:04:40,530 --> 00:04:47,120
[inquisitive music playing]

63
00:05:10,018 --> 00:05:13,146
[in English] <i>Abel Merelli, this is</i>
<i>the First Striker of the Philippine Army.</i>

64
00:05:13,229 --> 00:05:15,189
<i>Stay still and raise your arms.</i>

65
00:05:15,273 --> 00:05:17,066
<i>You are surrounded.</i>

66
00:05:28,745 --> 00:05:33,124
[somber music playing]

67
00:05:36,544 --> 00:05:39,255
[in English] Merelli, don't move!

68
00:05:39,338 --> 00:05:42,550
[in English] I knew it.
You don't sell crabs.

69
00:05:42,633 --> 00:05:45,428
[in English] I'm Captain Padua
of the Armed Forces of the Philippines.

70
00:05:46,179 --> 00:05:49,474
By authority of the Antiterrorism Council
of the Philippines,

71
00:05:50,475 --> 00:05:51,851
you will be detained.

72
00:05:51,934 --> 00:05:53,269
We have evidence linking you

73
00:05:53,352 --> 00:05:55,605
to financing some terrorist groups
in South East Asia.

74
00:05:56,981 --> 00:05:58,274
I said don't move!

75
00:05:58,858 --> 00:06:00,693
[in English] You'll really
go to hell first.

76
00:06:01,486 --> 00:06:03,446
[beeping in distance]

77
00:06:08,701 --> 00:06:11,245
[stirring music playing]

78
00:06:39,023 --> 00:06:40,858
FATHER'S LANE
FOOD HUB IN BACLARAN

79
00:06:40,942 --> 00:06:44,320
[suave music playing]

80
00:07:19,105 --> 00:07:22,442
MAIN TITLE

81
00:07:32,910 --> 00:07:34,537
[in English] You made it, sir.

82
00:07:36,998 --> 00:07:38,291
[Mercado, in English] Good job, Padua.

83
00:07:39,167 --> 00:07:40,960
It's been five hours since the mission.

84
00:07:42,086 --> 00:07:45,173
Merelli is currently
being transferred to our camp.

85
00:07:45,756 --> 00:07:47,758
for detainment and debriefing.

86
00:07:49,010 --> 00:07:50,094
Where's Elaine?

87
00:07:52,805 --> 00:07:53,890
Where is she?

88
00:07:53,973 --> 00:07:55,349
[in English] Elaine who?

89
00:07:56,267 --> 00:07:57,393
Um…

90
00:08:08,362 --> 00:08:09,614
Elaine?

91
00:08:13,868 --> 00:08:16,579
[pensive music continues]

92
00:08:23,878 --> 00:08:25,171
What are you doing here?

93
00:08:25,254 --> 00:08:26,964
Did Elaine ever tell you she was leaving?

94
00:08:27,048 --> 00:08:28,132
No.

95
00:08:31,135 --> 00:08:33,346
Why would she suddenly leave?

96
00:08:34,096 --> 00:08:36,599
What exactly do you want from Elaine?

97
00:08:36,682 --> 00:08:37,975
Are you her stalker?

98
00:08:38,643 --> 00:08:41,187
She told me you can't be trusted.

99
00:08:41,270 --> 00:08:43,397
She also told me
you were faking your amnesia.

100
00:08:45,483 --> 00:08:49,111
I heard you got into
a shoot out at the beach.

101
00:08:50,696 --> 00:08:52,365
I also heard you killed the foreigner.

102
00:08:53,950 --> 00:08:55,201
Who are you, really?

103
00:08:55,284 --> 00:08:56,661
Are you a criminal?

104
00:08:56,744 --> 00:08:58,454
Hold up! What's with all the questions?!

105
00:09:00,081 --> 00:09:01,165
Sir, please, don't hurt me.

106
00:09:01,249 --> 00:09:02,750
I still want to get married.

107
00:09:07,421 --> 00:09:11,801
[pensive music continues]

108
00:09:24,480 --> 00:09:27,316
[in English] Padua, excellent work.

109
00:09:27,400 --> 00:09:29,360
They had been looking for him for months,

110
00:09:29,443 --> 00:09:31,320
but you're the only one
who could confirm his location.

111
00:09:32,113 --> 00:09:33,823
[in English] I just did
what had to be done, sir.

112
00:09:33,906 --> 00:09:36,158
[in English] You're being reassigned
to the South Sector Command.

113
00:09:37,076 --> 00:09:39,245
Debrief will be expedited.

114
00:09:39,328 --> 00:09:42,665
[in English] Actually, sir, um,
I wanna consult you

115
00:09:42,748 --> 00:09:44,625
because I'm thinking of taking a leave.

116
00:09:45,376 --> 00:09:46,711
[in English] Perhaps, even…

117
00:09:48,879 --> 00:09:50,464
Even early retirement, sir.

118
00:09:52,758 --> 00:09:54,260
Is this because of Elaine?

119
00:09:55,011 --> 00:09:57,638
[mellow music playing]

120
00:10:32,340 --> 00:10:34,342
You're close to your mother, aren't you?

121
00:10:34,925 --> 00:10:36,302
Isn't it obvious?

122
00:10:39,055 --> 00:10:41,349
But you don't have
a picture with your father.

123
00:10:42,975 --> 00:10:44,602
I bet you're mad at him.

124
00:10:44,685 --> 00:10:49,065
[mellow music continues]

125
00:10:57,865 --> 00:10:59,200
Why is that?

126
00:11:04,413 --> 00:11:07,208
Did your father cheat on your mother?

127
00:11:12,588 --> 00:11:13,964
I wish that were the case.

128
00:11:14,840 --> 00:11:16,967
That would have been better.

129
00:11:18,010 --> 00:11:20,388
But what if your father…

130
00:11:21,806 --> 00:11:23,182
was actually a monster?

131
00:11:27,728 --> 00:11:29,355
One whose absence from this world

132
00:11:31,399 --> 00:11:33,818
would somehow lessen my burdens.

133
00:11:36,445 --> 00:11:38,739
Wow, that's some deep anger
you have toward your father.

134
00:11:39,824 --> 00:11:41,409
But I get you.

135
00:11:42,701 --> 00:11:44,036
Come to think of it…

136
00:11:45,663 --> 00:11:49,125
The very people meant
to guide us toward what's right

137
00:11:50,334 --> 00:11:52,211
are often the ones in the wrong.

138
00:11:53,796 --> 00:11:56,382
And so, our life compass gets lost,

139
00:11:59,927 --> 00:12:01,804
sending us drifting to who knows where.

140
00:12:06,600 --> 00:12:08,644
But at least, you've escaped,

141
00:12:09,812 --> 00:12:10,813
instead of becoming like him.

142
00:12:13,732 --> 00:12:15,609
But how long will you keep running?

143
00:12:18,571 --> 00:12:21,031
Until you're strong enough to face them.

144
00:12:23,576 --> 00:12:25,953
Until you finally have
the guts to tell them…

145
00:12:28,080 --> 00:12:29,415
what they've done to you.

146
00:12:31,750 --> 00:12:35,671
[mellow music continues]

147
00:12:56,484 --> 00:12:59,153
[bus revving]

148
00:13:01,780 --> 00:13:04,617
[mellow music continues]

149
00:13:04,700 --> 00:13:06,535
SIR DELFIN'S
TAILORING SHOP

150
00:13:06,619 --> 00:13:09,997
[sewing machine whirring]

151
00:13:10,080 --> 00:13:13,709
I'll just take these blazers
to the dry cleaner tomorrow, okay?

152
00:13:13,792 --> 00:13:15,294
I need to go home soon anyway.

153
00:13:15,377 --> 00:13:17,213
I still have to cook dinner.

154
00:13:18,255 --> 00:13:19,924
Um… Anyway…

155
00:13:20,966 --> 00:13:22,968
I thought you were going
to tell Sir Delfin?

156
00:13:23,052 --> 00:13:24,887
You can handle it.

157
00:13:24,970 --> 00:13:26,931
He'd just get annoyed with me anyway.

158
00:13:27,014 --> 00:13:28,599
Also, please stop gossiping.

159
00:13:29,099 --> 00:13:31,185
Emerson, why aren't you done yet?!

160
00:13:31,268 --> 00:13:33,395
Delfin, Emerson said he wants
to get a cash advance.

161
00:13:34,063 --> 00:13:35,356
[mumbles]

162
00:13:35,439 --> 00:13:36,857
[Delfin] Seriously?

163
00:13:36,941 --> 00:13:38,943
He just asked for one the other month.

164
00:13:39,026 --> 00:13:40,694
I'm not his bank.

165
00:13:42,196 --> 00:13:43,948
I'll leave it to you.

166
00:13:44,698 --> 00:13:46,825
[Emerson clears throat] Ah…

167
00:13:47,409 --> 00:13:48,536
Um…

168
00:13:48,619 --> 00:13:49,745
[Emerson clears throat]

169
00:13:51,247 --> 00:13:52,289
Ah… Uh…

170
00:13:52,957 --> 00:13:54,124
Ah… Uh…

171
00:13:54,750 --> 00:13:57,920
Sir Delfin, do you happen to have…

172
00:13:59,129 --> 00:14:00,256
some extra cash for me?

173
00:14:00,339 --> 00:14:02,258
I'm guessing you might,

174
00:14:02,341 --> 00:14:04,009
since you're on your own in life.

175
00:14:04,093 --> 00:14:05,511
[chuckles softly]

176
00:14:06,804 --> 00:14:09,682
[glum music playing]

177
00:14:11,016 --> 00:14:12,977
On the contrary,

178
00:14:13,060 --> 00:14:17,982
Miss Cita told me
that you do have a child.

179
00:14:18,607 --> 00:14:21,026
What was his name again?

180
00:14:21,110 --> 00:14:23,028
Was it Atoy?

181
00:14:23,112 --> 00:14:24,154
Where is he now?

182
00:14:27,157 --> 00:14:29,577
I also can't help but notice that…

183
00:14:30,536 --> 00:14:32,371
you don't have a picture of him
here in your shop.

184
00:14:33,622 --> 00:14:34,790
What does he look like?

185
00:14:38,502 --> 00:14:41,046
What if I just dock a bit off your salary?

186
00:14:41,130 --> 00:14:44,008
Oh, Sir Delfin, I'm just messing with you.

187
00:14:44,091 --> 00:14:45,551
I'm already barely getting by.

188
00:14:46,886 --> 00:14:49,471
[glum music playing]

189
00:14:55,561 --> 00:14:56,520
Here, take it.

190
00:14:57,980 --> 00:14:59,982
Go find something better to do.

191
00:15:00,065 --> 00:15:01,901
[glum music continues]

192
00:15:06,113 --> 00:15:08,741
Hmm. This will do, I guess.

193
00:15:09,867 --> 00:15:12,411
[glum music continues]

194
00:15:25,132 --> 00:15:27,718
[children beatboxing]

195
00:15:27,801 --> 00:15:30,846
<i>♪ Yo! Welcome to Barang Tabang Lupa! ♪</i>

196
00:15:30,930 --> 00:15:32,514
<i>♪ You ready? I'm ready! ♪</i>

197
00:15:32,598 --> 00:15:34,600
<i>♪ The fiesta's just around the corner</i>
<i>The streets are alive! ♪</i>

198
00:15:34,683 --> 00:15:37,269
<i>♪ All for our patron</i>
<i>Saint Anthony of Padua ♪</i>

199
00:15:37,353 --> 00:15:38,562
<i>♪ Hope there's lechon on the table ♪</i>

200
00:15:38,646 --> 00:15:40,439
<i>♪ On top of Miss Nena's barbecue ♪</i>

201
00:15:40,522 --> 00:15:42,441
<i>♪ The vibes are solid!</i>
<i>Off-limits to pessimists ♪</i>

202
00:15:42,524 --> 00:15:44,860
<i>♪ No room for killjoys!</i>
<i>Break it down, yo! ♪</i>

203
00:15:44,944 --> 00:15:48,030
[groovy music playing]

204
00:15:48,113 --> 00:15:50,074
[feet pattering]

205
00:16:23,440 --> 00:16:25,776
[gentle music continues]

206
00:16:52,761 --> 00:16:54,888
- [man] Oh, be careful.
- [Julie] Over here.

207
00:16:54,972 --> 00:16:57,349
Atoy. Atoy, come on.

208
00:16:57,433 --> 00:16:58,767
- Hurry.
- [Julie chuckles softly]

209
00:17:01,311 --> 00:17:02,938
[Julie chuckles softly]

210
00:17:03,522 --> 00:17:04,523
[man] Watch your step.

211
00:17:07,151 --> 00:17:08,527
[Julie chuckles]

212
00:17:16,660 --> 00:17:20,289
The new statue of San Antonio de Padua!

213
00:17:20,372 --> 00:17:21,665
It's stunning!

214
00:17:21,749 --> 00:17:24,334
This will go right here in the church.

215
00:17:24,418 --> 00:17:26,378
Thank you so much, Julie,
for your generous donation.

216
00:17:26,462 --> 00:17:28,172
Oh, it's truly nothing.

217
00:17:28,255 --> 00:17:30,174
You know, the face and hands of the patron

218
00:17:30,257 --> 00:17:33,052
are crafted from legally acquired ivory.

219
00:17:33,135 --> 00:17:34,845
Oh, wow… This must have cost a fortune!

220
00:17:34,928 --> 00:17:36,680
You shouldn't have, Julie.

221
00:17:36,764 --> 00:17:39,141
No, it's perfectly fine.
I've been saving for years

222
00:17:39,224 --> 00:17:41,602
to make this happen.

223
00:17:41,685 --> 00:17:43,979
Saint Anthony has always been

224
00:17:44,063 --> 00:17:45,689
such a huge part of our lives,

225
00:17:45,773 --> 00:17:47,191
and I wanted this to be truly special.

226
00:17:47,274 --> 00:17:49,777
Father, if you don't mind me sharing.

227
00:17:49,860 --> 00:17:52,488
Julie and I have been praying
to Saint Anthony,

228
00:17:52,571 --> 00:17:54,364
asking for a blessing
so she could conceive.

229
00:17:54,448 --> 00:17:55,407
Truth be told,

230
00:17:55,991 --> 00:17:58,577
Julie's devotion to Saint Anthony
helped her conceive Atoy.

231
00:17:58,660 --> 00:18:02,915
Oh, Atoy, did you inherit
any traits from Saint Anthony?

232
00:18:02,998 --> 00:18:06,210
Are… Are you naturally good
at finding lost things?

233
00:18:06,293 --> 00:18:09,171
I'm the one who always manages to find

234
00:18:09,254 --> 00:18:10,881
Dad's missing buttons and scissors

235
00:18:10,964 --> 00:18:12,132
in the tailor shop.

236
00:18:12,216 --> 00:18:13,592
You really are something.

237
00:18:13,675 --> 00:18:16,261
I can't believe you exposed
how careless I am in front of Father.

238
00:18:16,345 --> 00:18:18,222
- Oh my.
- Seriously, Father…

239
00:18:18,305 --> 00:18:19,807
My son is a talented one.

240
00:18:20,599 --> 00:18:23,268
Atoy has a bright future ahead of him.

241
00:18:23,352 --> 00:18:26,230
[chuckles] Anyway,
I'll step away for a moment.

242
00:18:26,313 --> 00:18:27,231
All right, Father.

243
00:18:27,314 --> 00:18:28,315
To set this up properly.

244
00:18:28,398 --> 00:18:29,608
- [Julie] Okay.
- Oh, Boni.

245
00:18:29,691 --> 00:18:30,943
Come with me.

246
00:18:32,069 --> 00:18:33,112
[Julie chuckles] Okay.

247
00:18:35,781 --> 00:18:39,827
Saint Anthony, you have
always been our anchor.

248
00:18:40,536 --> 00:18:42,246
Please don't abandon us.

249
00:18:42,329 --> 00:18:45,457
If any trials come our way,

250
00:18:45,541 --> 00:18:49,253
make our family strong and whole.

251
00:18:49,336 --> 00:18:51,004
[Atoy and Delfin] Amen.

252
00:18:51,088 --> 00:18:54,133
[gentle music continues]

253
00:19:03,684 --> 00:19:04,726
Atoy?

254
00:19:05,435 --> 00:19:06,979
- Atoy, is that you?
- Father!

255
00:19:07,604 --> 00:19:09,106
- Father Peping.
- Oh.

256
00:19:09,189 --> 00:19:10,065
Ah, oh…

257
00:19:10,149 --> 00:19:11,400
Father.

258
00:19:11,483 --> 00:19:12,317
[clears throat]

259
00:19:12,401 --> 00:19:14,570
Wow, you look completely different!

260
00:19:15,445 --> 00:19:18,198
How old were you the last time I saw you?

261
00:19:18,282 --> 00:19:20,117
Ah…

262
00:19:21,160 --> 00:19:23,328
Around 20, I think.
Twenty, or 21 years old.

263
00:19:23,412 --> 00:19:24,746
Somewhere around that age, Father.

264
00:19:24,830 --> 00:19:27,207
Your father never mentioned
that you would come back.

265
00:19:27,708 --> 00:19:29,751
Yes, I never told anyone.

266
00:19:29,835 --> 00:19:31,795
Delfin will surely be pleased.

267
00:19:32,504 --> 00:19:34,756
You know, Atoy, as we grow older,

268
00:19:34,840 --> 00:19:36,383
we come to truly appreciate the value

269
00:19:36,466 --> 00:19:38,927
of the Ten Commandments.

270
00:19:39,011 --> 00:19:40,721
"Honor thy father and thy mother."

271
00:19:40,804 --> 00:19:42,097
- And…
- I agree, Father.

272
00:19:42,181 --> 00:19:43,807
Anyway, I'll go ahead now,

273
00:19:43,891 --> 00:19:46,560
before our conversation
turns into a full homily.

274
00:19:46,643 --> 00:19:48,061
Thank you. It was nice seeing you,
Father Peping.

275
00:19:48,145 --> 00:19:48,979
Always take care.

276
00:19:49,062 --> 00:19:51,440
There's actually a couple more.
"Thou shall not kill."

277
00:19:51,523 --> 00:19:53,442
- [chuckles]
- "Don't commit adultery."

278
00:19:53,525 --> 00:19:54,526
I'll go ahead now, Father.

279
00:20:01,200 --> 00:20:05,037
- [indistinct chatter]
- [suave music playing]

280
00:20:05,120 --> 00:20:07,206
- [clacks]
- Oh!

281
00:20:07,289 --> 00:20:11,460
[indistinct chatter]

282
00:20:11,543 --> 00:20:14,588
[suave music continues]

283
00:20:14,671 --> 00:20:16,673
[Noel] Karla!

284
00:20:16,757 --> 00:20:19,384
- Karla!
- Paldo, Paldo…

285
00:20:19,468 --> 00:20:21,345
Not so fast. What have you done this time?

286
00:20:21,428 --> 00:20:23,013
- Noel!
- Karla, get over here.

287
00:20:23,096 --> 00:20:25,182
- Noel, what do you want?
- Come here! I'll make your hand bleed!

288
00:20:25,265 --> 00:20:26,642
Paldo, help, help!

289
00:20:26,725 --> 00:20:28,644
You're done for! You're in big trouble!

290
00:20:28,727 --> 00:20:30,062
Don't hurt your child.

291
00:20:30,145 --> 00:20:31,063
Leave it to me instead!

292
00:20:31,146 --> 00:20:32,231
No way!

293
00:20:32,314 --> 00:20:33,607
No wonder she's so stubborn.

294
00:20:33,690 --> 00:20:35,692
- That's enough!
- [clamoring]

295
00:20:35,776 --> 00:20:37,694
Cut it out! I said enough!

296
00:20:37,778 --> 00:20:40,197
Do you really want your child
to grow up spoiled, huh?

297
00:20:40,280 --> 00:20:42,324
- [clamoring]
- Stop it!

298
00:20:42,407 --> 00:20:44,409
- Do it!
- Help!

299
00:20:44,493 --> 00:20:45,744
- [crowd] Do it! Do it! Do it!
- Help! Help!

300
00:20:45,827 --> 00:20:50,374
[suave music continues]

301
00:20:52,626 --> 00:20:54,461
- Hit her! Hit her!
- You're enabling her!

302
00:20:54,544 --> 00:20:56,755
- I'll talk to her!
- It's no surprise she's acting this way.

303
00:20:56,838 --> 00:20:58,048
Move! Move!

304
00:20:58,131 --> 00:21:00,259
- Hey!
- That's enough!

305
00:21:00,342 --> 00:21:02,636
- Hey! Hey! Karla!
- Stop! That's enough!

306
00:21:02,719 --> 00:21:04,513
- Go after her, hurry!
- Enough!

307
00:21:04,596 --> 00:21:06,515
- Don't let her get away!
- Karla! Karla!

308
00:21:06,598 --> 00:21:08,350
- Hey!
- Karla!

309
00:21:08,433 --> 00:21:11,478
[clamoring]

310
00:21:12,354 --> 00:21:13,897
- Stop it! Enough!
- Out of my way!

311
00:21:13,981 --> 00:21:14,940
[Cita] I said…

312
00:21:15,023 --> 00:21:16,692
[Cita] I said that's enough!

313
00:21:19,611 --> 00:21:20,696
Atoy?

314
00:21:20,779 --> 00:21:22,447
- You take care of that!
- Karla…

315
00:21:23,699 --> 00:21:24,700
Oh…

316
00:21:25,909 --> 00:21:26,743
Atoy?

317
00:21:27,327 --> 00:21:29,204
Is eating breakfast
not a thing here anymore?

318
00:21:29,288 --> 00:21:30,455
Hey, Atoy.

319
00:21:31,290 --> 00:21:32,791
That kid did something wrong.

320
00:21:33,375 --> 00:21:35,502
She managed to steal
some money again, Atoy.

321
00:21:35,585 --> 00:21:37,838
You shouldn't be taking her side at all.

322
00:21:37,921 --> 00:21:40,215
You should've kept your money well hidden.

323
00:21:40,299 --> 00:21:43,135
Atoy… You literally just got home.

324
00:21:43,218 --> 00:21:45,053
Stay out of this, bro!

325
00:21:45,137 --> 00:21:46,013
Paldo.

326
00:21:46,096 --> 00:21:47,472
Your name means "winner",

327
00:21:47,556 --> 00:21:48,432
but you sure don't act like one.

328
00:21:48,515 --> 00:21:50,350
- Take it easy.
- Bleh!

329
00:21:50,434 --> 00:21:51,268
- Oh, you!
- Cut it out…

330
00:21:51,351 --> 00:21:53,186
- Hey!
- Sir…

331
00:21:53,270 --> 00:21:54,813
What you're doing is child abuse.

332
00:21:54,896 --> 00:21:56,440
Stay out of this.

333
00:21:56,523 --> 00:21:57,607
[exclaims]

334
00:21:57,691 --> 00:21:58,775
[crashes]

335
00:21:59,568 --> 00:22:01,570
Noel! Noel!

336
00:22:02,404 --> 00:22:04,573
You can take him to the morgue now.

337
00:22:04,656 --> 00:22:06,158
Oh wait, I meant the ER.

338
00:22:06,908 --> 00:22:08,660
Darn you, Atoy!

339
00:22:09,911 --> 00:22:13,623
[crowd clamoring]

340
00:22:13,707 --> 00:22:17,711
[brazen music continues]

341
00:22:17,794 --> 00:22:20,589
[crashes]

342
00:22:20,672 --> 00:22:21,840
[thudding]

343
00:22:21,923 --> 00:22:26,887
[crowd clamoring]

344
00:22:26,970 --> 00:22:29,139
- Paldo, it's not worth it.
- [crowd] Atoy! Atoy!

345
00:22:29,222 --> 00:22:30,640
[thuds]

346
00:22:30,724 --> 00:22:32,726
[crowd] Wow!

347
00:22:35,270 --> 00:22:37,230
Emerson, are you heading back already?

348
00:22:37,314 --> 00:22:39,900
Yes, I still have
a lot of suits to deliver.

349
00:22:39,983 --> 00:22:41,234
No one is going to keep
an eye on the shop.

350
00:22:41,318 --> 00:22:43,236
Cita is on her day off as well.

351
00:22:43,320 --> 00:22:45,238
[Emerson on phone]
<i>The traffic in Divisoria is horrible.</i>

352
00:22:45,322 --> 00:22:47,949
I was also sent out to get

353
00:22:48,033 --> 00:22:49,701
zippers and buttons.

354
00:22:49,785 --> 00:22:51,369
Are you eating those?

355
00:22:51,453 --> 00:22:54,206
- Sold out immediately?!
- [suave music playing]

356
00:22:54,289 --> 00:22:55,957
You better hurry home.

357
00:22:56,708 --> 00:23:00,170
And look at all the mistakes
you made on Sir Lucky's suit.

358
00:23:00,670 --> 00:23:02,672
Honestly, I can't tell

359
00:23:02,756 --> 00:23:04,549
if the machine was defective

360
00:23:04,633 --> 00:23:07,094
or if the tailor's brain was just crooked.

361
00:23:07,177 --> 00:23:09,971
Oh, Sir Delfin,
you're way too harsh on me.

362
00:23:10,055 --> 00:23:11,932
Actually, I did my very best.

363
00:23:12,015 --> 00:23:13,058
Best?

364
00:23:13,141 --> 00:23:15,352
Well, your best is not good enough.

365
00:23:15,435 --> 00:23:17,437
Huh? Just get over here already!

366
00:23:17,521 --> 00:23:18,480
Yes, I'll be on my way.

367
00:23:19,606 --> 00:23:21,441
Sir Delfin! Sir Delfin!

368
00:23:21,525 --> 00:23:22,692
Karla, what is it?

369
00:23:22,776 --> 00:23:25,320
Paldo and the others
are ganging up on Atoy.

370
00:23:26,488 --> 00:23:27,405
Who, Atoy?

371
00:23:27,489 --> 00:23:29,241
Yes, he's already here.

372
00:23:29,324 --> 00:23:32,160
[pleasant music playing]

373
00:23:32,244 --> 00:23:35,664
- [crowd clamoring]
- [thudding]

374
00:23:35,747 --> 00:23:40,669
[crowd clamoring]

375
00:23:40,752 --> 00:23:42,879
Stop it! That's enough!

376
00:23:42,963 --> 00:23:44,506
[thuds]

377
00:23:45,924 --> 00:23:46,925
What's wrong with you?

378
00:23:47,008 --> 00:23:48,885
You were gone for so many years.

379
00:23:49,469 --> 00:23:52,389
And now, you've come back
just to stir trouble!

380
00:23:53,140 --> 00:23:56,935
[somber music playing]

381
00:23:59,104 --> 00:24:00,981
Delfin, Atoy only tried to help.

382
00:24:01,773 --> 00:24:05,360
You know Paldo's group,
they're always looking for trouble.

383
00:24:05,443 --> 00:24:06,653
Don't blame it on me.

384
00:24:06,736 --> 00:24:07,988
Atoy's the one meddling.

385
00:24:08,071 --> 00:24:12,159
Hey, Paldo, I know exactly what you are.
You've been a troublemaker since day one.

386
00:24:13,285 --> 00:24:14,494
That's the point!

387
00:24:14,578 --> 00:24:15,871
That's it! He already knows Paldo!

388
00:24:15,954 --> 00:24:17,706
So, he should've just stayed out of it.

389
00:24:17,789 --> 00:24:20,333
None of this would have happened
if it weren't for this child!

390
00:24:20,417 --> 00:24:22,836
- Let's go!
- [Cita] What's wrong?

391
00:24:22,919 --> 00:24:24,254
Hold on. What's…

392
00:24:24,337 --> 00:24:25,380
Why are you taking it out on the child?

393
00:24:25,463 --> 00:24:26,756
She stole money again!

394
00:24:26,840 --> 00:24:28,925
That child is hopeless!

395
00:24:29,009 --> 00:24:30,802
[pensive music playing]

396
00:24:30,886 --> 00:24:33,722
- How much did she take?
- I'm innocent!

397
00:24:33,805 --> 00:24:35,390
- Five hundred pesos.
- What?

398
00:24:35,473 --> 00:24:37,350
[scoffs]

399
00:24:38,185 --> 00:24:39,269
Give me a moment.

400
00:24:39,352 --> 00:24:40,478
Here, take it.

401
00:24:40,562 --> 00:24:43,607
You can keep the change.

402
00:24:43,690 --> 00:24:45,275
Just don't hurt your child again.

403
00:24:46,776 --> 00:24:47,944
Sure.

404
00:24:48,028 --> 00:24:50,447
What about us, Sir Delfin?

405
00:24:50,530 --> 00:24:52,282
Karla has already ruined our day.

406
00:24:52,365 --> 00:24:53,867
[man] That's right! Look around you!

407
00:24:53,950 --> 00:24:55,660
Ask him for money then.

408
00:24:55,744 --> 00:24:58,330
Atoy, damages!

409
00:24:58,413 --> 00:25:00,207
- Please!
- Now, wait a second.

410
00:25:00,290 --> 00:25:01,625
Stop! Stop! Enough!

411
00:25:01,708 --> 00:25:02,918
I'm really sorry.

412
00:25:03,001 --> 00:25:04,294
Just head home now. Go ahead.

413
00:25:04,377 --> 00:25:05,545
Allow me to accompany you.

414
00:25:05,629 --> 00:25:07,380
You still have work later. Let's go.

415
00:25:07,464 --> 00:25:09,007
I can manage!

416
00:25:09,716 --> 00:25:11,676
And make sure
you warn your godchild, okay?

417
00:25:11,760 --> 00:25:15,555
Good thing she and I didn't grow up
at the same time, or else… [chuckles]

418
00:25:16,223 --> 00:25:17,557
I'm heading home!

419
00:25:17,641 --> 00:25:18,975
All right, I've got somewhere to be too.

420
00:25:20,352 --> 00:25:22,520
I'll just go with you, Sir Delfin.

421
00:25:25,482 --> 00:25:29,236
[mellow music playing]

422
00:25:29,319 --> 00:25:30,403
You've bought so much.

423
00:25:30,487 --> 00:25:32,113
Dad!

424
00:25:32,989 --> 00:25:33,990
My hair!

425
00:25:38,870 --> 00:25:41,206
All right, then,
you all should head home too!

426
00:25:41,289 --> 00:25:43,166
[crowd clamoring]

427
00:25:43,250 --> 00:25:44,584
Miss Cita.

428
00:25:44,668 --> 00:25:48,004
[mellow music continues]

429
00:25:50,423 --> 00:25:51,967
- [Atoy] Godmother.
- [Cita] Oh?

430
00:25:52,050 --> 00:25:54,761
I apologize for what happened
to Godfather Noel.

431
00:25:54,844 --> 00:25:56,012
[chuckles]

432
00:25:56,721 --> 00:25:58,056
It's fine.

433
00:25:58,139 --> 00:26:00,517
Let him get roughed up once in a while.

434
00:26:00,600 --> 00:26:02,519
He deserves it.

435
00:26:03,645 --> 00:26:05,772
Why do you even put up with him?

436
00:26:05,855 --> 00:26:08,108
He's still Karla's father.

437
00:26:08,191 --> 00:26:10,944
I guess Noel really is my karma.

438
00:26:11,027 --> 00:26:13,655
Let's not talk about him anymore.

439
00:26:13,738 --> 00:26:16,449
Also, you never told us
you were going home.

440
00:26:16,533 --> 00:26:18,243
How long will you be staying here?

441
00:26:20,161 --> 00:26:21,288
[in English] It depends.

442
00:26:21,913 --> 00:26:25,292
Hopefully it's for good,
so your dad has someone by his side.

443
00:26:25,375 --> 00:26:26,751
Just bear with him.

444
00:26:27,335 --> 00:26:29,087
He's happy you're home too.

445
00:26:29,170 --> 00:26:31,131
He just doesn't show it.

446
00:26:31,214 --> 00:26:35,844
[sentimental music playing]

447
00:26:38,013 --> 00:26:40,140
[man shouting indistinctly]

448
00:26:41,266 --> 00:26:43,643
Nothing much seems to have changed here.

449
00:26:43,727 --> 00:26:45,103
- Actually, some things have.
- [funky music playing]

450
00:26:45,186 --> 00:26:47,897
Do you remember Bunda Boy?

451
00:26:47,981 --> 00:26:48,857
Mmm.

452
00:26:48,940 --> 00:26:50,942
- He's called Bunda Girl now!
- [Bunda Girl chuckling]

453
00:26:51,026 --> 00:26:52,819
On top of that, she's a nurse too.

454
00:26:52,902 --> 00:26:55,280
Sometimes, I have her
check my blood pressure.

455
00:26:55,363 --> 00:26:56,489
[in English] Oh my…

456
00:26:56,573 --> 00:26:57,824
Atoy!

457
00:26:57,907 --> 00:27:00,618
- Oh, hey.
- What a surprise!

458
00:27:01,286 --> 00:27:02,537
Me? A surprise? I beg to disagree…

459
00:27:02,620 --> 00:27:03,955
- You're the real grand surprise!
- [laughs]

460
00:27:04,039 --> 00:27:05,749
Hold on.

461
00:27:05,832 --> 00:27:07,292
Come on, let's go over there.

462
00:27:07,375 --> 00:27:10,253
[chuckles] Atoy!

463
00:27:12,422 --> 00:27:14,132
[Nestor] I'd like to buy some ice!

464
00:27:14,215 --> 00:27:15,216
Anybody home?

465
00:27:15,300 --> 00:27:16,134
SIR DELFIN'S TAILORING SHOP

466
00:27:16,217 --> 00:27:17,761
I'd like to buy some ice, please.

467
00:27:18,595 --> 00:27:20,263
Hello?!

468
00:27:20,347 --> 00:27:22,640
- Nestor!
- I'd like to anybody?

469
00:27:22,724 --> 00:27:23,767
Nestor, over here.

470
00:27:23,850 --> 00:27:26,603
The ice seller's at the next corner!

471
00:27:26,686 --> 00:27:29,105
Goodness, you're drunk again!

472
00:27:29,189 --> 00:27:30,815
Your liver must be begging for mercy.

473
00:27:30,899 --> 00:27:32,150
[stammers]

474
00:27:32,233 --> 00:27:34,027
- Oh…
- Sir Delfin?

475
00:27:34,110 --> 00:27:34,944
Sir…

476
00:27:35,028 --> 00:27:37,322
- They don't sell ice…
- Oh, oh, come on, over here.

477
00:27:37,405 --> 00:27:38,239
Over here.

478
00:27:38,323 --> 00:27:40,241
Over here, come on.

479
00:27:43,244 --> 00:27:45,246
- Atoy…
- Yes?

480
00:27:45,330 --> 00:27:46,790
I see you've returned.

481
00:27:48,375 --> 00:27:49,501
Come on.

482
00:27:49,584 --> 00:27:50,835
It's time to go home.

483
00:27:59,260 --> 00:28:00,845
Atoy, I'm still talking to you.

484
00:28:01,638 --> 00:28:03,890
[Atoy] <i>Dad, you can't stop me</i>
<i>from leaving anymore.</i>

485
00:28:04,557 --> 00:28:05,683
I've already passed.

486
00:28:05,767 --> 00:28:07,560
I'm joining the army.

487
00:28:08,311 --> 00:28:09,813
- [scoffs]
- [somber music playing]

488
00:28:09,896 --> 00:28:11,731
Why didn't you tell me about it?

489
00:28:11,815 --> 00:28:14,526
I can't believe
it took you this long to tell me!

490
00:28:14,609 --> 00:28:17,070
What do you think of me?

491
00:28:17,153 --> 00:28:19,239
Am I nothing in this home?

492
00:28:20,407 --> 00:28:21,449
Atoy!

493
00:28:21,950 --> 00:28:23,618
I'm still your father!

494
00:28:24,744 --> 00:28:28,873
I don't want you to be a soldier,
and I won't allow it!

495
00:28:28,957 --> 00:28:30,542
Your mother just passed away.

496
00:28:30,625 --> 00:28:32,460
Wait a minute.

497
00:28:32,544 --> 00:28:34,754
Why are you in such a hurry to leave, huh?

498
00:28:34,838 --> 00:28:35,839
Why?!

499
00:28:36,548 --> 00:28:38,883
Because I don't want to be with you!

500
00:28:38,967 --> 00:28:40,719
Hold on, hold on.

501
00:28:42,512 --> 00:28:43,972
What have I ever done to you, huh?

502
00:28:44,055 --> 00:28:46,766
What have I done to you?
Why are you treating me like this?

503
00:28:47,642 --> 00:28:49,561
Atoy!

504
00:28:49,644 --> 00:28:51,563
When you leave now,

505
00:28:52,522 --> 00:28:54,232
don't you ever come back!

506
00:28:57,193 --> 00:29:01,281
[somber music continues]

507
00:29:09,706 --> 00:29:12,459
Is it even right for me to come back here?

508
00:29:14,919 --> 00:29:15,920
Atoy.

509
00:29:16,671 --> 00:29:18,131
This is your home.

510
00:29:19,090 --> 00:29:21,217
This is where your parents raised you.

511
00:29:22,844 --> 00:29:25,430
Make peace with your father for now.

512
00:29:26,097 --> 00:29:28,433
Put aside the fight,
at least for a while, all right?

513
00:29:35,064 --> 00:29:40,987
- [electronic blipping]
- [intense music playing]

514
00:29:44,866 --> 00:29:47,577
Mel, did someone move Saint Anthony?

515
00:29:47,660 --> 00:29:48,495
Where's the statue?

516
00:29:48,578 --> 00:29:51,039
- Our patron has been taken, Sir Delfin.
- [woman] My God…

517
00:29:51,122 --> 00:29:52,499
It's just simple.

518
00:29:52,582 --> 00:29:55,293
Because if there was
no break-in from the outside,

519
00:29:55,376 --> 00:29:57,253
that means the thief must have

520
00:29:57,337 --> 00:29:58,546
stayed inside, right?

521
00:29:58,630 --> 00:30:00,215
Do any of you know someone
who eats biscocho?

522
00:30:00,298 --> 00:30:03,176
I saw someone eating that yesterday.

523
00:30:03,259 --> 00:30:05,512
We can't arrest Paldo

524
00:30:05,595 --> 00:30:08,348
unless he confesses,
and we don't even have solid proof

525
00:30:08,431 --> 00:30:11,601
that he's the one who took the statue!

526
00:30:12,477 --> 00:30:13,520
[Marcus, in English] <i>A container truck…</i>

527
00:30:13,603 --> 00:30:15,438
This is what they used
to take Saint Anthony.

528
00:30:15,522 --> 00:30:17,023
‪UP NEXT

529
00:30:18,399 --> 00:30:19,818
Who are you?

530
00:30:23,112 --> 00:30:25,698
Subtitle translation by:
Inocencio Cañete Raman Jr.
